          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>National Timing Resilience and Security Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Transportation to provide for the establishment, sustainment, and operation of a complement to and backup&nbsp;for the timing component of the Global Positioning System (GPS).&nbsp;(GPS satellites contain atomic clocks that provide precise time data and allow GPS receivers to synchronize to those clocks.) The system must:&nbsp;(1) reduce critical dependencies on the GPS network; (2) ensure the availability of uncorrupted and non-degraded timing signals for military and civilian users if GPS timing signals are corrupted or otherwise unavailable; and (3) be land-based, operational&nbsp;in 2 years, and capable of operation for 20 years. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
